WEBVTT

00:51.415 --> 00:54.779
-

01:02.525 --> 01:03.590
Ree?

01:05.132 --> 01:06.494
Ree?

01:07.596 --> 01:08.760
Wake up, baby.

01:14.537 --> 01:16.273
They wanna hear you sing.

01:19.146 --> 01:19.771
You wanna sing?

01:20.708 --> 01:21.641
Yes, please.

01:22.545 --> 01:23.742
All right.

01:35.459 --> 01:37.756
Clarence,
Ella's looking for you.

01:38.693 --> 01:40.165
Wait here, Ree.

01:40.200 --> 01:42.299
-I'll be right back.
-Okay.

01:42.334 --> 01:43.465
They butchered
my essay.

01:43.500 --> 01:44.433
Took all the politics out.

01:44.468 --> 01:45.797
Can you believe that?

01:45.832 --> 01:48.272
Communism is absolutely
for the Negro.

01:48.307 --> 01:49.834
How else are we gonna have
everything we ever wanted?

01:49.869 --> 01:51.143
Now, how does
a man with one eye

01:51.178 --> 01:52.144
play like he has four hands?

01:53.312 --> 01:54.608
You been practicing?

01:54.643 --> 01:56.247
Yes, Mr. Tatum.

01:56.282 --> 01:57.809
She could hit
three octaves easy.

01:57.844 --> 02:00.680
You know, you the finest
looking cat here, right?

02:00.715 --> 02:02.550
Nigga, I know that.

02:02.585 --> 02:03.815
What else you got?

02:08.261 --> 02:09.821
Hey, Ree.

02:09.856 --> 02:11.328
Hey, Uncle Sam.

02:11.363 --> 02:13.363
No more segregated
clubs for me.

02:13.398 --> 02:14.826
I'm not walking through
no one's kitchen

02:14.861 --> 02:16.861
to get to the stage.

02:16.896 --> 02:20.337
I said to them,
"I'm so happy to be
performing in England,

02:20.372 --> 02:21.569
but just remember

02:21.604 --> 02:23.241
there's only one Heaven,
one Earth,

02:23.276 --> 02:24.836
and one queen.

02:24.871 --> 02:26.904
Me. Dinah Washington."

02:28.743 --> 02:30.710
"That Elizabeth on y'alls
throne is an imposter."

02:30.745 --> 02:32.745
-You didn't.
-Oh, yes, I did.

02:32.780 --> 02:35.352
-And I made 'em bow before me.
-

02:35.387 --> 02:37.420
Well, look out, y'all.

02:38.225 --> 02:39.686
The entertainer is here.

02:40.227 --> 02:41.622
Hi.

02:41.657 --> 02:43.360
He said he wanted
a race novel.

02:43.395 --> 02:45.791
Sure, he desegregated
the army.

02:45.826 --> 02:47.298
But he didn't do
a damn thing after that.

02:47.333 --> 02:49.861
-Hi, Aunt Ella. Uncle Duke.
-Hey.

02:49.896 --> 02:51.599
You ready, Ree?
Come on.

02:57.772 --> 03:00.377
Everyone.

03:00.412 --> 03:02.643
Everyone.

03:02.678 --> 03:05.877
For those of you visiting
my home for the first time,

03:06.814 --> 03:10.552
this is my daughter, Aretha.

03:10.587 --> 03:13.291
She'd like to sing
a little something for you.

03:13.326 --> 03:14.457
What would you
like to sing, Ree?

03:15.988 --> 03:17.922
How old is she?

03:17.957 --> 03:19.693
She's 10,

03:19.728 --> 03:21.926
but her voice's
going on 30, honey.

03:21.961 --> 03:24.566
Aretha would
like to perform

03:24.601 --> 03:26.634
My Baby Likes to Bebop.

03:26.933 --> 03:28.471
Damn!

03:28.506 --> 03:29.934
I was gonna record that
on my next album.

03:31.674 --> 03:33.278
Can we do a duet?

03:43.422 --> 03:46.654
'Cause my baby likes to bebop

03:55.830 --> 03:56.829
Sing, baby!

04:08.711 --> 04:12.416
Do a dance and a flip-flop

04:12.451 --> 04:15.320
Like the hepcats do

04:15.355 --> 04:18.553
"My baby likes to bebop"

04:43.548 --> 04:45.042
Back to bed with you.

04:56.495 --> 04:59.859
Go marching in

04:59.894 --> 05:02.664
Those white folks don't know
what to do with her.

05:02.699 --> 05:04.369
Sock it to 'em, Clara!

05:04.404 --> 05:05.535
Yeah, Grandma!

05:05.570 --> 05:08.406
Sock it to 'em!
Sock it to 'em!

05:16.911 --> 05:17.844
Momma's here!

05:22.719 --> 05:23.883
Momma!
-

05:26.052 --> 05:29.020
God! Babe,
I missed you so much.

05:29.957 --> 05:31.396
Hi! Momma!

05:33.092 --> 05:34.498
Mommy!

05:35.963 --> 05:37.336
My babies!

05:37.998 --> 05:39.866
My precious!

05:50.846 --> 05:52.384
Come on, let's go! Let's go!

05:52.419 --> 05:53.649
-Let's go!
- Bye, Grandma!

05:53.684 --> 05:54.815
Come on, baby!

05:54.850 --> 05:55.849
Let's go in the car!

05:59.855 --> 06:03.956
That way

06:03.991 --> 06:07.663
In the morning sun

06:07.698 --> 06:11.898
The night is new

06:34.021 --> 06:35.559
Sing another one, Momma!

06:35.594 --> 06:37.759
Oh, Ree,
that's the third song now.

06:37.794 --> 06:39.629
Please?

06:39.664 --> 06:40.960
No, I want to talk.

06:40.995 --> 06:42.797
Please?
-Oh, God.

06:43.503 --> 06:44.898
Oh, all right.

06:45.868 --> 06:48.440
What if I sing-talk, hmm?

07:03.820 --> 07:04.918
We praising
the Lord, Momma!

07:06.658 --> 07:08.086
-

07:08.121 --> 07:09.220
-

07:09.256 --> 07:10.990
-

07:21.541 --> 07:23.871
You still singing
at the Saturday night parties?

07:23.906 --> 07:25.037
Yeah.

07:25.072 --> 07:26.907
Mmm. Don't say "yeah".

07:26.942 --> 07:29.811
"Yeah" is common. Say "yes".

07:29.846 --> 07:30.944
Yes.

07:31.584 --> 07:32.946
You enjoy it?

07:32.981 --> 07:34.783
-Yeah. Yes.
-Uh-uh.

07:36.248 --> 07:39.018
Look at me, Ree.

07:39.053 --> 07:41.691
If you ever don't
want to sing, don't.

07:41.726 --> 07:42.890
I love singing.

07:42.925 --> 07:44.595
No, I know. I know.

07:46.830 --> 07:49.633
Your daddy doesn't
own your voice, Ree.

07:49.668 --> 07:51.998
Nobody does but God.

07:53.067 --> 07:55.870
And you don't ever
have to fear any man.

07:57.236 --> 07:58.741
You understand?

08:01.075 --> 08:03.548
You are so worthy, Ree.

08:03.583 --> 08:05.880
Don't you ever let anybody
tell you otherwise.

08:06.817 --> 08:08.047
Yes, Momma.

08:12.724 --> 08:14.086
Oh, Ree, don't cry.

08:14.121 --> 08:15.923
Come on, I'll see you
for your birthday.

08:15.958 --> 08:17.056
Three weeks is a long time.

08:17.091 --> 08:19.861
I know, but I am
always with you.

08:19.896 --> 08:21.500
Even when I'm not there.

08:21.865 --> 08:23.029
Okay?

08:28.839 --> 08:30.036
Go.

08:42.985 --> 08:45.557
Ree, get back here!

08:48.056 --> 08:49.121
Ree!

08:52.258 --> 08:53.092
Goodbye!

08:57.670 --> 08:59.065
Bye, Momma!

09:03.973 --> 09:05.104
We're marching
Marching up to Zion

09:08.747 --> 09:09.680
Ree?

09:10.078 --> 09:11.110
Ree?

09:13.081 --> 09:15.312
I'm the oldest. I should be
in the front of the line.

09:15.347 --> 09:16.115
Hush.

09:18.955 --> 09:20.823
We have nothing
to fear, church.

09:22.288 --> 09:25.762
'Cause what is the white man
compared to God?

09:29.229 --> 09:32.164
What is any law, any injustice

09:32.199 --> 09:34.870
compared to the power
of our Lord?

09:38.370 --> 09:42.845
'Cause He will deliver us
from the den like Daniel.

09:44.178 --> 09:47.311
And Daniel went
into that lion's den.

09:48.248 --> 09:51.689
Daniel went into
that lion's den.

09:51.724 --> 09:53.889
-Yes, Jesus!
-Not yelling,

09:53.924 --> 09:55.693
nor fussing.

09:55.728 --> 09:56.892
Not crying!

09:56.927 --> 09:58.894
-Not complaining!
-No!

09:58.929 --> 10:00.324
Praising the Lord!

10:00.359 --> 10:02.832
-Yeah!
-'Cause he knew

10:02.867 --> 10:04.636
the Lord was with him.

10:04.671 --> 10:07.199
He feared no man!

10:07.234 --> 10:09.036
Can you hear me, church?

10:09.071 --> 10:10.774
I wish somebody
would pray with me

10:10.809 --> 10:12.776
-'cause He will!
-He will!

10:12.811 --> 10:14.239
He will!
-He will!

10:14.274 --> 10:17.374
He will shut the jaws
of segregation,

10:17.409 --> 10:19.178
and any man, person,

10:19.213 --> 10:21.686
or institution that would dare

10:21.721 --> 10:23.655
stand against us.

10:23.690 --> 10:26.350
He took us from slavery,

10:26.385 --> 10:29.727
he took us from
the valley of reconstruction.

10:29.762 --> 10:31.729
- Freedom!

10:31.764 --> 10:33.390
-Freedom!
- Freedom!

10:33.425 --> 10:34.831
Freedom!

10:34.866 --> 10:36.195
-Freedom!
- Freedom!

10:36.230 --> 10:38.967
Freedom now!
Praise Him! Praise Him!

10:39.002 --> 10:41.772
-Preach, Daddy, preach!
- Hallelujah.

10:50.717 --> 10:52.750
Hey? Ree?

10:52.785 --> 10:54.818
Ree!

10:54.853 --> 10:56.721
How come
you're not singing tonight?

10:57.724 --> 10:59.317
Daddy didn't ask me to.

11:00.892 --> 11:02.793
What's your doll's name?

11:06.392 --> 11:07.963
Dee.

11:07.998 --> 11:10.669
Mmm. That's a pretty name.

11:13.036 --> 11:15.036
You're pretty, too.

11:15.071 --> 11:16.433
What's your boyfriend's name?

11:16.468 --> 11:18.941
I don't have
a boyfriend.

11:19.878 --> 11:21.845
I can be your boyfriend.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.209
Would you like that?

11:24.410 --> 11:26.212
We'll have fun.

11:58.378 --> 11:59.982
Come on, Ree!

12:01.920 --> 12:03.150
I don't want to.

12:03.185 --> 12:04.789
Ree, I will beat your behind.

12:10.258 --> 12:11.961
What are you doing?

12:11.996 --> 12:13.424
I don't care if you beat me.

12:13.459 --> 12:15.228
I don't want my hair done.

12:15.263 --> 12:17.032
Don't you wanna look pretty
for church tomorrow?

12:17.067 --> 12:18.902
No!

12:18.937 --> 12:20.266
Y'all wait in the living room.

12:21.203 --> 12:23.170
Come on.

12:23.205 --> 12:24.435
Don't sweat out all my work.

12:24.470 --> 12:26.140
That's gotta last you
all week!

12:28.540 --> 12:30.012
Sit down.

12:35.382 --> 12:37.151
You wanna tell me
what's wrong?

12:39.353 --> 12:40.418
Ree-Ree?

12:47.130 --> 12:49.933
I know you don't
wanna tell me,

12:49.968 --> 12:53.101
but you can always
tell the Lord, Ree.

12:53.136 --> 12:55.301
He loves you, no matter what.

13:28.534 --> 13:31.304
You're supposed
to be in bed, Ree.

13:31.339 --> 13:35.913
my every burden

13:35.948 --> 13:37.079
Come, come and join me
for a while.

13:46.926 --> 13:51.489
Whoa, yes

13:53.031 --> 13:54.360
What if I wasn't here?

13:58.036 --> 14:00.531
What do you mean by that?

14:03.173 --> 14:06.306
-I don't know.
-

14:11.984 --> 14:13.478
Hello?

14:13.513 --> 14:14.985
See how nicely
their voices are blending?

14:16.087 --> 14:18.120
They let Sam
take the proper lead.

14:19.618 --> 14:24.291
Too many members of our choir
try to stand out

14:24.326 --> 14:25.457
instead of supporting
the soloist.

14:25.492 --> 14:26.458
Clarence?

14:28.363 --> 14:30.066
Come to the phone.

14:32.103 --> 14:34.466
-Play this next.
-Okay.

14:37.009 --> 14:38.305
Right back.

14:43.279 --> 14:45.510
Barbara's dead.
- How?

14:45.545 --> 14:47.479
Heart attack.

14:52.090 --> 14:54.453
I'll tell them
in the morning, Mama.

14:54.488 --> 14:57.324
No. No, you cannot
wait till tomorrow

14:57.359 --> 15:00.327
to tell them
their momma is dead.

15:00.362 --> 15:01.559
-

15:06.104 --> 15:07.367
No. No.

15:09.008 --> 15:10.073
Ree?

15:34.297 --> 15:35.494
Ree?

15:46.672 --> 15:48.342
I'm sorry, baby.

15:50.280 --> 15:52.511
Let's go inside.

16:14.073 --> 16:19.439
dear Ree-Ree

16:25.711 --> 16:27.513
Come on now, Ree.

16:31.189 --> 16:33.024
She just miss her momma.

16:33.059 --> 16:34.355
They all missin' her,

16:34.786 --> 16:37.193
but how long
she gonna keep silent?

16:37.228 --> 16:38.623
Goin' on three weeks.
She gotta...

16:38.658 --> 16:41.527
She just needs a little time.
That's all.

16:41.727 --> 16:43.067
Ree?

16:44.466 --> 16:48.732
Miss Clara made you
this beautiful cake,

16:48.767 --> 16:50.668
and Reverend James
came especially for you.

16:51.374 --> 16:53.209
What do you say, Ree?

16:56.610 --> 16:58.049
Do you say, "Thank you"?

16:59.481 --> 17:00.579
-Do you say something?
-

17:02.286 --> 17:03.714
Make a wish, Ree.

17:07.621 --> 17:08.587
I can't do this.

17:11.426 --> 17:14.395
Come on.
- Momma. Momma.

17:14.430 --> 17:15.560
Come on, baby. It's all right.

17:15.596 --> 17:16.561
-Momma. Momma.
-It's all right.

17:16.597 --> 17:18.564
-Come on, baby.
-Momma.

17:18.598 --> 17:22.469
-

17:29.775 --> 17:31.544
Why are you hiding over there?

17:31.579 --> 17:33.645
Come on over here
and get your lesson.

17:34.681 --> 17:36.681
You know this one.

17:37.816 --> 17:40.355
Tell you what,
I'll be the choir

17:40.390 --> 17:41.719
and you play the lead.

17:45.428 --> 17:46.823
Three, four...

17:58.804 --> 18:01.541
Ree is helping me
with my arrangement.

18:01.576 --> 18:02.740
I see.

18:03.875 --> 18:05.776
Has she spoken to you?

18:05.811 --> 18:08.614
that far

18:12.422 --> 18:16.589
Do you think you can
stay silent forever, Ree? Hmm?

18:21.695 --> 18:22.760
Look at me.

18:26.832 --> 18:29.536
We must honor the gifts
that God has given us, Ree.

18:31.177 --> 18:34.772
You will be singing
in church tomorrow.

18:36.908 --> 18:39.381
James, can you prepare her?

18:40.417 --> 18:42.318
Yes, sir.

18:42.353 --> 18:43.583
Thank you.

19:07.543 --> 19:09.807
Don't let nothin' come between
you and your music, Ree.

19:13.384 --> 19:15.681
Music will save your life.

19:21.623 --> 19:23.656
God holds our hand.

19:23.691 --> 19:24.723
Yeah!
-Through Him,

19:24.758 --> 19:27.198
we can do anything!

19:27.233 --> 19:28.595
He's a catcher!

19:28.630 --> 19:30.663
A dream catcher!

19:30.698 --> 19:32.335
Amen!

19:32.370 --> 19:33.501
Amen.
- Amen.

19:35.439 --> 19:37.241
And now,

19:37.276 --> 19:40.640
my daughter Aretha
will bless us with song.

21:03.021 --> 21:08.497
-
guilty stains

21:11.062 --> 21:17.341
Lose all their
guilty stains
-

21:17.376 --> 21:20.608
-

21:40.564 --> 21:42.795
-

21:42.830 --> 21:44.599
-

21:51.839 --> 21:53.839
-

21:57.812 --> 22:02.980
running through the flood?

22:17.997 --> 22:20.503
I wonder,
do you feel all right?

22:20.538 --> 22:21.834
Yes!

22:21.869 --> 22:22.967
I said,
do you feel all right?

22:23.002 --> 22:24.507
Yes!

22:25.543 --> 22:27.004
Amen.

22:28.678 --> 22:31.646
I'm ecstatic to be able
to report to you

22:31.681 --> 22:34.979
that the day before yesterday,
we filled up the jail.

22:36.785 --> 22:39.115
We have already won a victory
here in Birmingham.

22:39.150 --> 22:40.391
Amen!

22:41.625 --> 22:43.526
Due, in no small part,

22:43.561 --> 22:46.089
to the valiant work
of our leader.

22:46.124 --> 22:48.960
A man whom I feel
honored to call my friend.

22:50.502 --> 22:54.867
The Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.

22:54.902 --> 22:58.409
All right! Yes, sir!
Yes, sir! Yes, sir!

23:03.845 --> 23:05.548
Come on! Somebody!

23:13.492 --> 23:15.888
Some people

23:15.923 --> 23:18.891
think that we are crazy

23:18.926 --> 23:20.893
for taking on this fight.

23:20.928 --> 23:22.466
Yes!

23:22.501 --> 23:25.832
But the forces against us
are strong,

23:25.867 --> 23:28.967
and they are determined
to stop us.

23:29.002 --> 23:33.103
But we are just
as determined to go on!

23:35.778 --> 23:37.943
Non-violently,

23:38.880 --> 23:41.111
with love.

23:41.146 --> 23:44.455
As long as it takes
to win our freedom.

23:44.490 --> 23:45.588
Yes!

23:46.791 --> 23:49.856
And Jesus is here with us
every single step of the way.

23:52.025 --> 23:53.464
Amen!

23:53.499 --> 23:54.432
Yes, sir!

23:56.029 --> 23:57.600
Uncle Martin...

23:57.635 --> 24:01.131
Now don't call me
Uncle Martin anymore.

24:01.166 --> 24:02.638
You make me feel old,
that's the problem.

24:02.673 --> 24:03.870
I want to march.

24:04.906 --> 24:06.609
Don't look at me
like I'm still a child.

24:06.644 --> 24:07.775
I'm not afraid.

24:07.810 --> 24:09.480
-Oh, you're not?
-No.

24:09.515 --> 24:10.910
Well, damn.

24:10.945 --> 24:12.912
Then you need to be
leadin' this movement

24:12.947 --> 24:15.013
and teaching me how to not be

24:15.048 --> 24:17.180
terrified of these
crazy white folks.

24:17.215 --> 24:19.490
Martin...
-

24:19.987 --> 24:22.053
Why do you want to march?

24:22.088 --> 24:25.023
After all this time
traveling with you,

24:25.058 --> 24:26.662
after all the horror
we've seen,

24:26.697 --> 24:27.993
what kind of question is that?

24:30.932 --> 24:32.965
Are you runnin'
from your daddy?

24:33.000 --> 24:34.065
No.

24:36.069 --> 24:39.675
So, you tell him
you wanna march?

24:39.710 --> 24:41.512
I don't have to.

24:41.547 --> 24:43.976
It's my decision.
I'm a grown woman, remember?

24:44.011 --> 24:48.651
Oh, so, you ready
to orphan your kids now, hmm?

24:48.686 --> 24:50.851
-Are you?
-No.

24:50.886 --> 24:51.852
But you're doing it anyway.

24:51.887 --> 24:54.184
Because I have to.

24:54.219 --> 24:55.955
-And I don't?
-Ree...

24:55.990 --> 24:57.957
Singing for the movement

24:57.992 --> 25:00.663
and sending people
into battle with a song

25:00.698 --> 25:02.797
is not enough anymore.

25:02.832 --> 25:03.963
I need to be with them.

25:04.966 --> 25:06.031
You have a good talk?

25:07.298 --> 25:08.704
Yes.

25:14.305 --> 25:16.041
It was a good talk.

25:16.879 --> 25:18.879
Brother, come on.

25:18.914 --> 25:20.980
She's restless, I can tell.

25:21.015 --> 25:23.180
I... I... I don't know
if it's restless.

25:24.249 --> 25:26.821
She just wants to do more.

25:26.856 --> 25:28.086
What kind of more?

25:39.165 --> 25:40.098
I'll be there in a minute.

25:43.609 --> 25:44.839
Momma!

25:44.874 --> 25:47.710
Clarence! Eddie!

25:47.745 --> 25:50.680
-Momma! Momma! Momma!
-My babies! My babies!

25:53.014 --> 25:54.717
-Are you all right, baby?
-

25:54.752 --> 25:57.918
Clarence, you go in your room
and wait for me.

25:57.953 --> 25:59.755
Come here. It's all right,
baby, it's all right.

25:59.790 --> 26:01.020
Come on. Come on.

26:01.055 --> 26:03.187
It's all right.
It's all right.

26:03.222 --> 26:05.860
Every time I come
back, they want me less.

26:05.895 --> 26:07.158
That's not true.

26:07.193 --> 26:09.732
They talk about you
all the time.

26:09.767 --> 26:12.064
Every night, I show 'em
where you are on the map.

26:12.671 --> 26:14.132
One cookie.

26:18.941 --> 26:20.006
Fix your face now.

26:20.712 --> 26:22.206
This party is for y'all.

26:22.241 --> 26:23.944
-How are you, Mama?
-God is good.

26:23.979 --> 26:25.143
All the time.

26:26.652 --> 26:28.212
Let's eat. I'm starving.

26:29.347 --> 26:31.248
-

26:32.790 --> 26:34.086
So, where y'all headed?

26:34.121 --> 26:37.155
We go to Tennessee,
then to Georgia,

26:37.190 --> 26:40.290
then to North Carolina,
and then back to Alabama,
I think.

26:40.325 --> 26:42.831
Damn. Martin's tour's busier
than Daddy's.

26:42.866 --> 26:46.637
Erma, sometimes we hit
two states in one day.

26:46.672 --> 26:50.333
What was that story about
Aunt Mahalia not paying you?

26:50.368 --> 26:53.908
She said I would receive
my reward in Heaven.

26:58.211 --> 26:59.342
Oh.

27:01.720 --> 27:03.148
No, Ree. Uh-uh.

27:13.831 --> 27:15.226
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh...

27:15.261 --> 27:16.865
-Smokey...
-Hey, hey, hey, hey.

27:16.900 --> 27:18.328
He's got some news, Ree.

27:18.363 --> 27:20.099
I heard
you're cuttin' a record.

27:20.134 --> 27:22.101
Yeah, with Berry
over at Motown.

27:22.136 --> 27:23.905
They got some
sweet sounds, Ree.

27:23.940 --> 27:25.434
They're signing a bunch of
folks in the neighborhood.

27:25.469 --> 27:27.942
Listen, we are trying
to put Detroit on the map.

27:27.977 --> 27:29.240
You gotta be a part of it.

27:29.275 --> 27:31.682
-I would love that.
-Yeah?

27:31.717 --> 27:33.145
Cecil, let me talk
to Daddy about it.

27:33.180 --> 27:34.817
Don't bring it up until I say.

27:34.852 --> 27:36.819
You know what?
Let's let Berry talk to him.

27:36.854 --> 27:38.249
Better yet, his sister.

27:38.284 --> 27:40.691
She can talk ice
out of the devil's mouth.

27:42.057 --> 27:43.320
What are you drinking?

27:44.125 --> 27:45.663
Iced tea.

27:47.128 --> 27:50.261
Just iced tea?

27:52.199 --> 27:55.200
-With a little bourbon.
-

27:56.742 --> 27:58.973
Yeah, you look
like a bourbon girl.

28:01.274 --> 28:02.845
How long are you in town for?

28:02.880 --> 28:04.011
A week.

28:04.046 --> 28:05.749
Then I return to Tennessee.

28:05.784 --> 28:07.377
Well, then,
I won't waste any time.

28:07.412 --> 28:08.917
Mm.

28:08.952 --> 28:11.722
-I'd like to take you out.
-Hmm.

28:11.757 --> 28:13.350
I'd like you to take me out.

28:13.891 --> 28:15.220
How about tonight?

28:16.487 --> 28:18.157
Ree!

28:18.192 --> 28:19.895
Come and help me
set this table.

28:21.833 --> 28:24.867
Yes, to tonight.

28:24.902 --> 28:27.232
-Okay.
-Excuse me a moment.

28:37.046 --> 28:39.211
Reverend.

28:39.246 --> 28:42.016
I put up with you coming
to my house all these years

28:42.051 --> 28:44.414
'cause you were friends
with my friends.

28:44.449 --> 28:46.416
But I don't want you
around here anymore.

28:46.451 --> 28:48.385
May I give you some counsel,
Reverend?

28:49.828 --> 28:52.191
Ephesians 6:4 says, "Fathers,

28:52.226 --> 28:54.424
do not exasperate
your children.

28:54.459 --> 28:56.228
Instead, bring them up
in the training

28:56.263 --> 28:58.329
and the instruction
of the Lord."

28:58.364 --> 29:00.067
Lord, give me strength.

29:00.102 --> 29:01.464
Are you serious?

29:01.499 --> 29:04.434
You may wanna loosen
your grip on Aretha.

29:04.469 --> 29:06.007
You know, every minister's
daughter I've ever known...

29:06.042 --> 29:07.404
Nigga, you don't
wanna mess with me...

29:08.341 --> 29:09.406
or mine.

29:30.836 --> 29:32.297
I got this.

29:33.102 --> 29:34.431
I got it.

29:42.914 --> 29:44.342
-

29:44.377 --> 29:45.816
Whoo!
-

29:45.851 --> 29:47.114
Whoo!

29:48.854 --> 29:50.953
I love to party

29:52.253 --> 29:54.286
I want you by my side

29:54.321 --> 29:55.452
Take that off.

29:59.931 --> 30:02.558
-Everyone! everyone!
-

30:02.593 --> 30:05.462
Please, please, gather around.

30:07.906 --> 30:09.807
Aretha, will you join me,
please?

30:15.144 --> 30:17.848
This party is not just, uh,

30:17.883 --> 30:19.311
a homecoming.

30:19.346 --> 30:22.413
It's also an announcement.

30:22.448 --> 30:26.417
God is moving us
on to our next chapter.

30:29.290 --> 30:31.455
I've been talking to a number
of record producers

30:31.490 --> 30:32.995
about Aretha.

30:33.030 --> 30:34.898
There were many

30:34.933 --> 30:36.361
who were interested
in working with her.

30:39.432 --> 30:41.531
Tell them what it is, Ree.

30:41.566 --> 30:42.400
Ah...

30:44.910 --> 30:46.404
A plane ticket
to New York City.

30:52.082 --> 30:53.510
Congratulations, Ree.

30:55.580 --> 30:57.415
Thank you.

31:01.355 --> 31:02.860
This is it.

31:04.325 --> 31:05.863
Wow.

31:07.625 --> 31:09.559
Excuse me?

31:09.594 --> 31:11.561
I have a meeting
with a John Hammond

31:11.596 --> 31:12.936
of Columbia Records.

31:12.971 --> 31:14.498
Sign in, please.

31:22.343 --> 31:23.914
You ready?

31:25.346 --> 31:27.049
-I'm ready.

31:33.486 --> 31:38.192
I've always seen Aretha
as more than a gospel singer.

31:38.227 --> 31:41.261
Well, clearly from her demo,
she's so much more.

31:43.001 --> 31:44.429
Stand up, Ree.

31:45.630 --> 31:47.564
Turn around.

31:49.238 --> 31:52.074
There can sometimes be
a lack of effortlessness

31:52.109 --> 31:53.603
of the kind you find

31:53.638 --> 31:57.277
in a Lena Horne
or a Dorothy Dandridge.

31:57.312 --> 32:00.610
But what Aretha lacks
in formal education,

32:00.645 --> 32:03.547
she more than makes up for
in experience.

32:03.582 --> 32:07.958
She has performed before every
type of crowd imaginable,

32:07.993 --> 32:11.456
from small churches
to audiences of thousands.

32:12.492 --> 32:13.491
You can sit down now, Ree.

32:20.401 --> 32:24.139
I... I'm curious.

32:25.703 --> 32:28.506
Who are your favorite artists?

32:28.541 --> 32:30.145
Dinah Washington.

32:30.741 --> 32:32.312
Ella Fitzgerald.

32:32.347 --> 32:33.951
-Hmm.
- Sam Cooke.

32:34.415 --> 32:35.480
All family friends.

32:36.549 --> 32:38.714
Sam would very much
like Aretha

32:38.749 --> 32:40.617
to sign with RCA.

32:41.290 --> 32:43.488
Well, we can't have that.

32:45.360 --> 32:47.525
Welcome

32:47.560 --> 32:49.098
to Columbia Records.

32:57.768 --> 32:59.141
Prove yourself

33:00.639 --> 33:02.540
as a jazz artist, and
everything else will follow.

33:02.575 --> 33:04.047
I understand.

33:04.082 --> 33:05.378
Wonderful.

33:15.456 --> 33:17.423
Are you ready, Aretha?

33:17.458 --> 33:19.557
-Yes, Mr. Hammond.
-Wonderful.

33:19.592 --> 33:21.196
The conductor
will point at you

33:21.231 --> 33:22.593
when he's ready
for you to begin.

33:36.213 --> 33:40.578
accentuate the positive

33:44.551 --> 33:48.058
to the affirmative

33:48.093 --> 33:49.389
with mister in-between

33:49.424 --> 33:50.456
She sounds wonderful,
doesn't she?

33:50.491 --> 33:51.721
She does.

33:51.756 --> 33:53.789
Like a black Judy Garland.

33:53.824 --> 33:55.593
up to the maximum

33:55.628 --> 33:59.234
down to the minimum

33:59.269 --> 34:02.666
pandemonium

34:02.701 --> 34:06.505
upon the scene

34:06.540 --> 34:08.243
Ladies and gentlemen,

34:08.277 --> 34:10.080
the Village Vanguard
is proud to present

34:10.114 --> 34:11.576
Miss Aretha Franklin,

34:11.610 --> 34:14.083
debuting her latest record,
Unforgettable.

34:21.554 --> 34:24.127
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

34:24.161 --> 34:26.591
We hope you enjoy
the show tonight.

34:27.396 --> 34:29.561
I see an old family friend.

34:29.596 --> 34:32.101
Dinah Washington
is in the audience.

34:39.440 --> 34:40.835
I'd like to sing a song

34:40.871 --> 34:44.641
in honor of her great artistry
and talent.

35:08.239 --> 35:09.799
Bitch!

35:09.834 --> 35:11.636
Don't you ever sing
the Queen's songs

35:11.671 --> 35:12.769
when the Queen
is in front of you!

35:22.352 --> 35:24.484
What the hell
were you thinking?

35:24.849 --> 35:26.288
I'm sorry.

35:26.323 --> 35:27.487
You wanna take me on?

35:27.522 --> 35:29.357
-No.
- Liar.

35:29.392 --> 35:30.886
You wouldn't be here if you
wasn't trying to replace me

35:30.921 --> 35:32.789
and every other bitch
out here singin'.

35:34.529 --> 35:35.891
How many albums have you had?

35:35.926 --> 35:36.859
Four.

35:38.335 --> 35:39.796
And no hits.

35:48.477 --> 35:50.510
You out here,
but I can see you

35:50.545 --> 35:52.512
still that little girl
in your daddy's living room.

35:52.547 --> 35:54.778
You're singin' everything
and anything.

35:54.813 --> 35:57.385
Shoop Shoop one day,
Skylark the next,

35:57.420 --> 35:59.717
and then some
Billie Holiday blues.

35:59.752 --> 36:01.290
Girl, you're all
over the place.

36:01.886 --> 36:02.819
What do you wanna sing?

36:03.954 --> 36:05.294
I don't know.

36:08.365 --> 36:09.727
You don't know?

36:09.762 --> 36:12.796
I want hits. I just want hits.

36:12.831 --> 36:14.732
Girl, you need to let go
of that "up with the race"

36:14.767 --> 36:17.405
Booker T. Washington
proper Negro shit.

36:17.440 --> 36:18.901
That's not you.

36:18.936 --> 36:20.606
Your daddy likes to pretend
that's who he is,

36:20.641 --> 36:22.608
but that's not
who he is either.

36:22.643 --> 36:25.215
Child, y'all church folks

36:25.250 --> 36:27.943
are some of the nastiest
people out here.

36:27.978 --> 36:30.517
Ray Charles told me
that the best sex he ever had

36:30.552 --> 36:32.222
was when he was singin'
on the gospel circuit.

36:33.819 --> 36:37.755
Honey, find the songs
that suit you. That move you.

36:37.790 --> 36:41.198
Until you do that,
you ain't goin' nowhere.

36:44.929 --> 36:46.533
Put some teabags on that.

36:47.668 --> 36:48.865
Take the puffiness down.

36:54.312 --> 36:55.542
How's Big Mama?

36:57.348 --> 36:58.611
She's all right.

36:58.976 --> 36:59.876
The kids?

37:01.550 --> 37:03.385
They're good.

37:03.420 --> 37:05.486
Child, you ever gonna tell us
who their daddy is?

37:36.849 --> 37:38.684
Ree-Ree?

37:38.719 --> 37:39.883
You wanna tell me
what's wrong?

37:39.918 --> 37:40.917
I can't.

38:12.489 --> 38:13.752
No answer.

38:14.524 --> 38:15.622
Call her again.

38:20.761 --> 38:21.660
Hmm.

38:23.093 --> 38:25.335
I didn't know you were
comin' in today, Daddy.

38:25.370 --> 38:26.798
You are 68 minutes late.

38:26.833 --> 38:29.999
Mr. Hammond
asked me to come in.

38:30.034 --> 38:33.904
You've been skipping
interviews and gigs.

38:34.940 --> 38:37.611
The demon is back.

38:37.646 --> 38:40.878
Ree has a tendency
to indulge her pain.

38:40.913 --> 38:43.078
Can we talk about this
somewhere else?

38:43.113 --> 38:45.047
John. John.

38:45.082 --> 38:48.556
It's important that you
understand that this behavior

38:48.591 --> 38:53.055
is not a reflection
of her upbringing or her race.

38:53.090 --> 38:54.760
Well, I've worked
with Bessie Smith

38:54.795 --> 38:55.959
and Billie Holiday.

38:55.994 --> 38:58.368
Aretha is a saint
in comparison.

38:58.403 --> 39:00.502
She wasn't raised in
a whorehouse like them.

39:00.537 --> 39:02.801
She was raised
in a proper home

39:02.836 --> 39:04.935
with every convenience
and luxury.

39:06.939 --> 39:10.776
But still, a darkness
would descend on her.

39:10.811 --> 39:12.415
I called it the demon.

39:12.450 --> 39:15.847
She'd lock herself away,
wouldn't speak, move,

39:15.882 --> 39:17.816
just wallow
in whatever imaginary...

39:18.489 --> 39:19.554
I...

39:22.119 --> 39:24.724
You told me before
we came out here

39:24.759 --> 39:25.659
that you had it under control.

39:25.694 --> 39:27.023
I have control.

39:29.159 --> 39:32.402
You keep complaining
that you don't have any hits.

39:32.437 --> 39:34.932
This is why
you don't have any hits.

39:34.967 --> 39:36.032
Acting like a trifling...

39:39.708 --> 39:40.971
Apologize to Mr. Hammond.

39:41.006 --> 39:43.072
No, there's no need
to apologize.

39:43.107 --> 39:45.844
That is not why
I don't have hits.

39:45.879 --> 39:47.043
You don't pick
good songs for me.

39:55.152 --> 39:57.592
Sorry for being late,
Mr. Hammond.

39:59.992 --> 40:01.596
It won't happen again.

40:03.193 --> 40:05.061
I'm ready to record
when you are.

40:05.800 --> 40:06.997
Hmm.

40:10.739 --> 40:13.443
Please excuse me while
I go to the ladies' room.

40:29.021 --> 40:31.593
So, you gonna come
with us this weekend?

40:31.628 --> 40:32.759
I have a gig.

40:32.794 --> 40:34.464
We can go after your gig.

40:35.192 --> 40:37.060
You work too hard.

40:37.095 --> 40:39.436
-Not according to my daddy.
-

40:40.670 --> 40:42.736
Well, you need some fun.

40:42.771 --> 40:43.968
Come with us.

40:52.044 --> 40:54.077
Can you introduce me
to his friend?

40:54.783 --> 40:56.046
I don't know him.

41:09.534 --> 41:11.193
-

41:21.810 --> 41:24.008
-

41:36.088 --> 41:38.726
You were supposed
to take me out in Detroit.

41:38.761 --> 41:40.090
Yes, one of my singers

41:40.125 --> 41:41.795
ran into a little trouble
out of town,

41:41.830 --> 41:44.193
so I had to take care of it.

41:44.228 --> 41:46.195
I think my father
said something to you

41:46.230 --> 41:48.835
-to make you reconsider.
-Oh.

41:48.870 --> 41:52.267
That's a nice little fable
you got goin' on in your head.

41:53.974 --> 41:55.105
I know what you do.

41:57.747 --> 41:59.241
It doesn't bother me.

42:00.783 --> 42:04.147
I know it doesn't bother you.

42:04.182 --> 42:07.084
You're rebelling against
your daddy.

42:07.119 --> 42:08.250
I don't mind.

42:09.253 --> 42:12.188
Listen, you wanna
use me for my body,

42:12.861 --> 42:14.861
you can use me, baby.

42:14.896 --> 42:17.226
You can wring me dry.

42:17.261 --> 42:20.031
You and me,
we've been through it.

42:21.001 --> 42:23.298
So we can skip all the flowers

42:23.333 --> 42:25.168
and the promises,
and the love bullshit,

42:25.203 --> 42:27.005
and just have some fun.

42:27.040 --> 42:28.842
I like fun.

42:28.877 --> 42:30.206
And we'll have plenty of it.

42:34.311 --> 42:36.014
I want one thing from you.

42:37.281 --> 42:38.115
What?

42:39.349 --> 42:41.019
To hear you sing.

42:41.054 --> 42:42.856
Just for me.

42:42.891 --> 42:45.023
What will I get in return?

42:45.828 --> 42:48.224
The best night of your life.

43:17.794 --> 43:18.925
Taxi!

43:36.010 --> 43:38.978
I want you to think about me
when you sing tomorrow.

43:39.013 --> 43:40.914
You're not coming home
with me?

43:41.411 --> 43:43.246
No.

43:43.281 --> 43:45.248
What about the best night
of my life?

43:45.283 --> 43:47.151
I didn't say
it would be tonight.

43:57.966 --> 44:02.001
enchanted boy

44:02.036 --> 44:08.073
Very far

44:30.999 --> 44:35.331
He passed my way

44:37.434 --> 44:38.939
I'm sorry.

44:40.008 --> 44:41.337
I'm sorry.

44:44.947 --> 44:46.848
Would you like
to take a break, Aretha?

44:47.345 --> 44:48.982
No.

44:49.017 --> 44:50.247
I'll get it right this time.

44:51.217 --> 44:52.414
Take 12.

45:11.237 --> 45:15.404
enchanted boy

45:15.439 --> 45:21.212
Very far

45:44.468 --> 45:48.470
he passed my way

45:48.505 --> 45:51.913
of many things

46:20.537 --> 46:22.438
You have all my records.

46:25.047 --> 46:26.409
You like them?

46:26.444 --> 46:27.443
I bought them.

46:29.986 --> 46:31.381
Which one you like best?

46:33.253 --> 46:34.384
They've all got something.

46:36.124 --> 46:37.827
Is this one your favorite?

46:40.128 --> 46:41.193
Hmm?

46:44.528 --> 46:45.934
Or this?

46:48.906 --> 46:50.268
What are you doing?

46:50.303 --> 46:51.874
Or this one?

46:51.909 --> 46:54.107
Went to 64 on the charts.

46:56.144 --> 46:58.012
You didn't even open this one.

47:00.445 --> 47:01.378
You don't like them?

47:02.282 --> 47:03.446
I didn't say that.

47:03.481 --> 47:04.986
Then say it.

47:05.021 --> 47:06.416
I won't be upset.

47:06.957 --> 47:08.990
No one does.

47:09.025 --> 47:11.861
First, I've listened
to all your albums.

47:12.589 --> 47:15.161
Including this one.

47:15.966 --> 47:17.427
More than once.

47:19.068 --> 47:22.135
Secondly, I love music.

47:22.170 --> 47:24.467
I take it seriously.

47:24.502 --> 47:27.305
I managed my first artist
when I was 15.

47:27.340 --> 47:31.045
Thirdly, what you
experienced yesterday,

47:31.080 --> 47:33.575
17 takes on one song?

47:33.610 --> 47:36.314
That happens to me
every time I hear you sing.

47:37.251 --> 47:39.416
My brain gets all...

47:40.584 --> 47:42.419
muddled.

47:42.454 --> 47:46.896
Well, first,

47:46.931 --> 47:50.526
my apologies for putting
you through so much pain.

47:53.102 --> 47:56.169
-And secondly...
-Mm-hmm.

47:56.204 --> 47:59.172
...you should have never told
me about your Achilles' heel.

48:00.340 --> 48:02.175
On our first date.

48:11.384 --> 48:13.318
Oh, damn it.

48:13.353 --> 48:16.288
-

48:20.624 --> 48:24.230
-Keep singing.
-

48:24.265 --> 48:25.968
I didn't think you were
comin' home for two weeks.

48:26.003 --> 48:27.464
-I miss my babies.
-

48:27.499 --> 48:28.971
And y'all.

48:31.041 --> 48:32.205
Who's that plate for?

48:33.274 --> 48:34.471
Ted.

48:34.506 --> 48:37.980
Oh, sweet Jesus,
are you serious?

48:38.015 --> 48:39.278
-What are you thinking?
-Please help me with Daddy.

48:39.313 --> 48:40.312
-No...
-Help me.

48:41.018 --> 48:42.182
Good Sunday, everybody.

48:48.322 --> 48:50.960
What the hell is this?

48:50.995 --> 48:52.522
You didn't tell them
I was coming?

48:52.557 --> 48:53.996
I don't know what you think
you're doing here

48:54.031 --> 48:55.096
and I don't care.

48:55.131 --> 48:57.263
Just leave. Now.

48:57.298 --> 48:58.627
Aretha asked me to come

48:58.662 --> 49:00.431
and Aretha
can ask me to leave.

49:01.731 --> 49:04.270
-I want him to stay.
-This is my house.

49:04.305 --> 49:05.634
Since when do
you get to tell me

49:05.669 --> 49:07.504
who gets to be in my house,
Ree, huh?

49:07.539 --> 49:09.506
I want you to get to know him.

49:09.541 --> 49:10.672
He's not what you think.

49:10.707 --> 49:11.706
Are you pregnant again?

49:11.741 --> 49:13.213
No!

49:14.348 --> 49:16.381
We just wanna be together.

49:18.055 --> 49:19.549
I love your daughter,
Reverend.

49:21.685 --> 49:24.026
And I think she loves me.

49:24.061 --> 49:25.390
I do.

49:25.425 --> 49:27.062
-No! No!
- Oh, my Lord!

49:27.097 --> 49:28.163
Ree...
- Clarence! No!

49:28.198 --> 49:30.197
Didn't I tell you
not to mess with me or mine?

49:30.232 --> 49:31.099
-Didn't I tell you?
-Clarence!

49:31.134 --> 49:32.463
Son, don't you let this man

49:32.498 --> 49:34.366
put your church
and your soul in jeopardy.

49:45.709 --> 49:46.983
Reverend,

49:48.316 --> 49:49.546
we have to figure this out.

49:49.581 --> 49:51.614
I'm not going anywhere.

49:51.649 --> 49:53.715
You can't see
through this hustler?

49:53.750 --> 49:56.751
-You're the greatest hustler
I ever seen.
-

49:56.786 --> 49:59.688
