about Aretha Franklin.

53:01.245 --> 53:04.246
-Mommy can't cook either.
-It's sticky!

53:06.910 --> 53:08.811
I'm gonna be honest with ya.

53:08.846 --> 53:11.847
Your version of Skylark
is one of my favorite songs.

53:12.553 --> 53:13.882
Thank you, Mr. Wexler.

53:13.917 --> 53:15.620
Oh, please, call me Jerry.

53:15.655 --> 53:17.391
You know what Etta James said
when she heard it?

53:17.426 --> 53:19.426
She said you pissed
all over that song,

53:19.461 --> 53:22.495
and she would never sing it
again in her entire life.

53:22.530 --> 53:24.497
You ruined that song
for Etta James.

53:24.532 --> 53:25.894
That is how good it was.

53:25.929 --> 53:27.632
And I'm not
bullshittin' ya, okay?

53:27.667 --> 53:28.566
A lot of these guys out here

53:28.602 --> 53:29.898
will say anything
to get in your drawers,

53:29.933 --> 53:31.537
but that's not me.

53:31.572 --> 53:33.671
I'm sorry.
All right, I'm crude.

53:33.706 --> 53:36.377
And you're a church girl,
and I should watch my mouth.

53:36.412 --> 53:37.642
I'm sorry.

53:38.612 --> 53:40.777
You do talk, don't ya?
Not just sing?

53:43.683 --> 53:45.320
You are
the sweetest thing, Aretha.

53:46.488 --> 53:48.554
I'd like you to call me
Miss Franklin.

53:48.589 --> 53:51.656
Okay, Miss Franklin.

53:51.691 --> 53:53.427
What songs would
you like to sing?

53:53.462 --> 53:55.264
I want hits.

53:55.299 --> 53:56.727
We're done
with standards.

53:56.762 --> 53:58.795
We want original songs
made for Aretha only.

53:58.830 --> 54:01.666
Great! We are speaking
the same language, my man.

54:01.701 --> 54:02.832
One of the songwriters
I represent

54:02.867 --> 54:04.537
